On April 29, 2022, the President signed into law H.R. 3113, known as the "Modernizing Access to Our Public Land Act." This law aims to digitize and make publicly available mapping data related to public access to Federal land and waters for outdoor recreation. The law is supported by Representatives Blake Moore, Fulcher, Neguse, and Schrier, as well as Senators Risch, King, Daines, Heinrich, Crapo, Manchin, Collins, Kelly, and Barrasso.